docs.text: Codex Atlanticus ¶ Codex Atlanticus [^1] is one of the history's most valuable book. Compiled in the 15 th Century[^2], it is a 12-volume, bound set of drawings and writings by Leonardo da Vinci , the largest single set. [^1] : Its name indicates the large paper used to preserve original Leonardo notebook pages, which was used for atlases. [^2] : Published in 1478. Status: #👨🏻‍🎨 Tags: [[art]] - [[history]] - [[tech]] - [[biology]] - [[science]] Date: ==[[2022-02-10]]==
docs.title: Codex Atlanticus
